      <div xml:id="NA224-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻiyāl pirivuṇarttappaṭṭa talaimakaḷ peyarttuñ col kaṭāvappaṭṭu “aṟivilātēm eṉṉai colliyum (G1+2: collum) piriyār ākārō” eṉṟu colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how SHE, who had been informed by the confidante of the separation, was again urged with a word [and] said “We have no knowledge. Even though [he? you?] speak to me, he will not separate, will he?”</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA224">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aṉpiṉar maṉṉum periya rataṉṟalaip</l>
<l>            piṉpaṉi yamaiyam varumeṉa muṉpaṉik</l>
<l>            koḻuntu muntuṟīik kuravarum piṉavē</l>
<l>            puṇarntīr puṇarmi ṉōveṉa viṇarmicaic</l>
<l>            ceṅka ṇiruṅkuyi letirkural payiṟṟu </l>
<l>            miṉpa vēṉilum vantaṉṟu namvayiṟ</l>
<l>            piriyala meṉṟu teḷittōr tēet</l>
<l>            tiṉiyevaṉ moḻikō yāṉē kayaṉaṟak</l>
<l>            kaṇṇaḻin tulaṟiya paṉmara neṭuneṟi</l>
<l>            viṉaimūcu kavalai vilaṅkiya </l>
<l>            vemmuṉai yaruñcura muṉṉi yōrkkē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The love of great people is something permanent.<note place="foot">Here it is impossible to decide whether SHE intends a general statement or whether she just talks of her own great love. The Tamil gives both in one.</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">On top of that</l>
<l>the Kura trees have budded, made to come as the fore-front</l>
<l rend="indent">of the early dewy season [which means]</l>
<l rend="indent4">the time of the later dewy season is coming.</l>
<l>And summer<note place="foot">Now even if one takes, with T.V.G., <term xml:lang="ta">vēṉil</term> to mean spring rather than summer, can it be <term xml:lang="ta">piṉpaṉi</term>, <term xml:lang="ta">muṉpaṉi</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">vēṉil</term> at the same time? Or is the point that SHE has been waiting already through all the three seasons?</note> has come with pleasure,</l>
<l rend="indent">when the voices of the red-eyed dark Koels echo each other</l>
<l rend="indent2">on top of the clusters, saying</l>
<l rend="indent2">“[now] unite, you who belong together”.</l>
<l>What shall I say now</l>
<l rend="indent2">to him who clearly said to us “we won’t separate”?</l>
<l rend="indent2">– to him who has approached the difficult desert with hot fronts</l>
<l rend="indent2">across the crossroads swarming with work(?),</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the long paths with many trees that have whithered</l>
<l rend="indent3">since the area perishes while the ponds are subsiding.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
